In a large skillet, brown pork chops in oil; sprinkle with salt. In a large saucepan, bring the water to a boil; add beans, carrots, potatoes with contents of sauce packet, soup, milk, butter and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to a boil. Transfer to a greased 13-in. x 9-in. x 2-in. baking dish; top with pork chops. Cover and bake at 350 degrees F for 25 minutes. Uncover; bake 5 minutes longer or until pork and vegetables are tender. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.